      "content": "I get that there are other views, but that's not what I need right now. I'm not looking for a debate, I'm looking for depth. \n\nCan you go deeper into the specific philosophical frameworks used to support the anti-regulation stance? Like, what are the actual principles—maybe something related to Mill's harm principle or libertarian notions of property rights—that people use to claim regulation is an inherent violation of speech? I need the technical, robust version of those arguments for my writing.",
